text: Albert Reynolds (3 November 1932 – 21 August 2014) was an Irish politician. He was Taoiseach of Ireland two terms in a row. He served from February 1992 to January 1993 and again from January 1993 to December 1994. He was the fifth leader of Fianna Fáil during the same period. In 1995, Reynolds was nominated for the Nobel Peace Prize. Reynolds died in Dublin, from complications from Alzheimer's disease, aged 81. ==References== Category:1932 births Category:2014 deaths Category:Deaths from Alzheimer's disease Category:Taoisigh of Ireland Category:Roman Catholics
